data.description: It is time to put all the HGTV-watching to work because this is a cosmetic renovation dream!!  Historic neighborhood right off Main Street, this property boasts more than half an acre lot with mature landscaping, gorgeous full-grown camellia bushes, vine-covered arbor and magnolia trees that with a little sprucing could be returned to a prized yard.  The entire floor plan is on one level constructed of brick and vinyl siding.  The home is covered with original wood flooring, solid wood panelled living room walls and updated bathrooms, plus new kitchen countertops.  The semi-open floor plan has a large formal living and dining room, a living room open to the kitchen, and an additional heated and cooled porch the current owner uses as the main living room and entertaining area.There are dual owner's suites, both with separate tubs and walk-in showers.  One owner's suite was added in the 1980's and is split from the other bedrooms and is large enough to create an in-law suite with its own outside access, double-sink vanity, jetted tub, and large walk-in closet and office area.  The other owner's suite is on the opposite side of the home and has a large bathroom, closet, and another bathroom that is currently being used as a closet, plus a massive walk-in closet.  This owner's suite is handicapped accessible with no ledge walk-in shower and open-bottom vanity.  Two additional bedrooms also have original wood flooring and share a full bathroom.  Outside, the huge backyard is so private with a firepit, vine-covered arbor, mature trees, deck, ramp for the deck, pebble covered patio area, and 2 sheds and a greenhouse.  There is even a covered patio for the grill!!  Bring some paint and creativity and you have the gem of the town.  Buyer to verify anything deemed important.  Roof was replaced in 2008.  Two TMS#'s will convey 1420103017 and 1420103021.  Marina is being constructed with ramps and dock facilities less than 3 miles on Lake Moultrie.  Bring your RV and boat and park it in your yard.  There are no covenants/restrictions.  Square footage is approximate and includes the add-ons.
